HEADWORD: Hidage
<hw>Hid"age</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <ets>hide</ets>
a quantity of land.]</ety> <fld>(O. Eng. Law.)</fld> <def>A tax formerly
paid to the kings of England for every hide of land.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>hydage</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

